    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt's not a problem.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt looks nicer.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"320\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42460975/215452554-a165105a-2a5d-438a-823f-8b964ca4acc5.png\">",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This shows the idea:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/statusline.c b/src/nvim/statusline.c\r\nindex de91bf334cdc..223089b960bb 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/statusline.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/statusline.c\r\n@@ -178,7 +178,8 @@ void win_redr_status(win_T *wp)\r\n   // May need to draw the character below the vertical separator.\r\n   if (wp->w_vsep_width != 0 && wp->w_status_height != 0 && redrawing()) {\r\n     if (stl_connected(wp)) {\r\n-      fillchar = fillchar_status(&attr, wp);\r\n+      // fillchar_status(&attr, wp);\r\n+      fillchar = utf_ptr2char(\"â–\");\r\n     } else {\r\n       fillchar = fillchar_vsep(wp, &attr);\r\n     }\r\n```\r\n\r\nConsiderations:\r\n\r\n- only makes sense if 'fillchars' \"stl\" flag is blank?\r\n- handle unfocused case\r\n- only when there is a vertical split",
